{"title":"Setting up a proxy for npm/yarn/nvm","uid":"82b9fceb41cc85f8f9d6f13639094390","slug":"npm-yarn","date":"2023-03-20T08:12:22.000Z","updated":"2025-11-26T03:08:04.069Z","comments":true,"path":"api/articles/npm-yarn.json","keywords":null,"cover":"https://img.kidwen.top/file/AgACAgUAAyEGAASHUuUOAAMRZ9bUSq45S9iA58u7TTZAUJE4_vkAAkjCMRvRCrhWEXuG9iWSOewBAAMCAAN5AAM2BA.png","content":"<p>npm stands for Node Package Manager. It’s a library and registry for JavaScript software packages. npm also has command-line tools to help you install the different packages and manage their dependencies.<br>\nYarn is a package manager that doubles down as project manager. Whether you work on one-shot projects or large monorepos, as a hobbyist or an enterprise user, we’ve got you covered.</p>\n<h2 id=\"NPM\">NPM</h2>\n<h3 id=\"Show-config\">Show config</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\"># show all config\nnpm config ls -l\n# or\nnpm get proxy\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-proxy-2\">Set proxy</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">npm config set proxy=http://127.0.0.1:10809\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Cancle-proxy-2\">Cancle proxy</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">npm config delete proxy\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-registry\">Set registry</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">npm config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-loglevel\">Set loglevel</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">npm config set loglevel http\n\n# or\n\nnpm install --loglevel=http\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"Yarn\">Yarn</h2>\n<h3 id=\"Show-config-2\">Show config</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">yarn config list\n# or\nyarn config get proxy\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-proxy-3\">Set proxy</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">yarn config set proxy http://127.0.0.1:10809\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Cancle-proxy-3\">Cancle proxy</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">yarn config delete proxy\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-registry-2\">Set registry</h3>\n<pre><code class=\"language-bash\">yarn config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"Nvm\">Nvm</h2>\n<h3 id=\"Show-proxy\">Show proxy</h3>\n<pre><code>nvm proxy\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Set-proxy-4\">Set proxy</h3>\n<pre><code>nvm proxy http://127.0.0.1:10809\n</code></pre>\n<h3 id=\"Cancle-proxy-4\">Cancle proxy</h3>\n<pre><code>nvm proxy none\n</code></pre>\n","text":"npm stands for Node Package Manager. It’s a library and registry for JavaScript ...","permalink":"/post/npm-yarn","photos":[],"count_time":{"symbolsCount":"1k","symbolsTime":"1 mins."},"categories":[{"name":"PROXY","slug":"PROXY","count":4,"path":"api/categories/PROXY.json"},{"name":"REGISTRY","slug":"PROXY/REGISTRY","count":1,"path":"api/categories/PROXY/REGISTRY.json"}],"tags":[{"name":"npm","slug":"npm","count":1,"path":"api/tags/npm.json"},{"name":"yarn","slug":"yarn","count":1,"path":"api/tags/yarn.json"}],"toc":"<ol class=\"toc\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#NPM\"><span class=\"toc-text\">NPM</span></a><ol class=\"toc-child\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Show-config\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Show config</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Set-proxy-2\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Set proxy</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Cancle-proxy-2\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Cancle proxy</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Set-registry\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Set registry</span></a></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Set-loglevel\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Set loglevel</span></a></li></ol></li><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-2\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Yarn\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Yarn</span></a><ol class=\"toc-child\"><li class=\"toc-item toc-level-3\"><a class=\"toc-link\" href=\"#Show-config-2\"><span class=\"toc-text\">Show config